#==========================================================
# USER CANCELLATION (Customer cancels their own booking)
#==========================================================

### 1. Cancel an Event Booking (User)
# The refund amount depends on the event's refundPolicy:
#   - "No Refund"       → Cancelled, refundAmount = 0
#   - "1 Day Before"    → Full refund if event starts > 24h from now
#   - "7 Days Before"   → Full refund if event starts > 7 days from now
POST {{baseUrl}}/booking/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "transactionId": "{{transactionId}}",
  "reason": "Cannot attend due to personal reasons"
}

### 2. Cancel a Course Booking (User)
POST {{baseUrl}}/booking/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "transactionId": "{{transactionId}}",
  "reason": "Schedule conflict with another commitment"
}

### 3. Cancel Without a Reason (Valid — reason is optional)
POST {{baseUrl}}/booking/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "transactionId": "{{transactionId}}"
}

#==========================================================
# ORGANIZER CANCELLATION — CANCEL ENTIRE EVENT
#==========================================================

### 4. Cancel Entire Event (Organizer — all bookings get full refund)
# This sets event.status → "Cancelled" and refunds ALL PAID bookings
# regardless of refund policy (organizer-initiated = full refund)
POST {{baseUrl}}/booking/cancel-event
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "{{eventId}}",
  "reason": "Event venue no longer available"
}

### 5. Cancel Entire Event Without Reason
POST {{baseUrl}}/booking/cancel-event
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "{{eventId}}"
}

#==========================================================
# ORGANIZER CANCELLATION — CANCEL ENTIRE COURSE
#==========================================================

### 6. Cancel Entire Course (Organizer — all bookings get full refund)
# This sets course.status → "Cancelled", cancels all batches,
# and refunds ALL PAID bookings
POST {{baseUrl}}/booking/cancel-course
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "courseId": "{{courseId}}",
  "reason": "Instructor unavailable"
}

#==========================================================
# ORGANIZER CANCELLATION — CANCEL SPECIFIC BATCH
#==========================================================

### 7. Cancel a Specific Batch (Only bookings in this batch get refunded)
# This sets batch.status → "Cancelled" but keeps the course active.
# Only transactions with this batchId are refunded.
POST {{baseUrl}}/booking/cancel-course
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "courseId": "{{courseId}}",
  "batchId": "{{batchId}}",
  "reason": "Not enough enrollment for this batch"
}

### 7b. Cancel a Specific Slot/Date of a Batch
# Organizer cancels only a specific date for an ongoing batch
POST {{baseUrl}}/booking/cancel-course
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "courseId": "{{courseId}}",
  "batchId": "{{batchId}}",
  "date": "2026-06-15",
  "reason": "Instructor unavailable for this day."
}

#==========================================================
# EDGE CASES & ERROR SCENARIOS
#==========================================================

### 8. Try to cancel an already-cancelled booking (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/booking/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "transactionId": "{{transactionId}}",
  "reason": "Trying again"
}

### 9. Try to cancel without transactionId (validation error)
POST {{baseUrl}}/booking/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "No transaction ID provided"
}

### 10. Try to cancel event as non-organizer (should fail with 403)
POST {{baseUrl}}/booking/cancel-event
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "{{eventId}}",
  "reason": "I'm not the organizer"
}

#==========================================================
# VIEW CANCELLED/REFUNDED TRANSACTIONS
#==========================================================

### 11. Get All My Tickets (includes CANCELLED and REFUNDED)
GET {{baseUrl}}/booking/list
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

### 12. Get Recent Bookings — Filter by CANCELLED status (Organizer)
GET {{baseUrl}}/booking/recent?status=CANCELLED&limit=10&page=1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 13. Get Recent Bookings — Filter by REFUNDED status (Organizer)
GET {{baseUrl}}/booking/recent?status=REFUNDED&limit=10&page=1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}


#==========================================================
# STRUCTURED CANCELLATION REASONS
#==========================================================

### 14. Get List of Cancellation Reasons (Customer)
GET {{baseUrl}}/booking/cancellation-reasons
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

### 15. Try to cancel with an invalid cancellation reason (should fail with 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/booking/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "transactionId": "{{transactionId}}",
  "reason": "Not an actual predefined reason"
}
